1
00:00:01,960 --> 00:00:05,920
ALL DEPICTED EVENTS ARE FICTIONAL

2
00:00:17,360 --> 00:00:21,000
<i>I just ran into this guy,</i>
<i>and he's so damn cute.</i>

3
00:00:21,080 --> 00:00:23,280
<i>His name is Qin.</i>
<i>From the College of Music.</i>

4
00:00:23,360 --> 00:00:25,360
If you rush in now, you're screwed.

5
00:00:25,440 --> 00:00:26,920
<i>Do your homework on him first.</i>

6
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:29,200
Help me.
Someone's following me.

7
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:32,960
<i>The fortune teller was right.</i>
<i>She said Qin would ask for help.</i>

8
00:00:33,040 --> 00:00:34,800
The prediction will come true.

9
00:00:34,880 --> 00:00:36,440
Gotta have each other's backs.

10
00:00:37,040 --> 00:00:39,640
<i>I've got a plan</i>
<i>for your confession, buddy.</i>

11
00:00:39,720 --> 00:00:42,440
Hey! I'm going to win your heart.

12
00:00:42,520 --> 00:00:45,040
<i>I'm not asking for permission.</i>
<i>Just letting you know.</i>

13
00:00:45,120 --> 00:00:48,080
<i>I feel like I've been enchanted</i>
<i>all because of your voice.</i>

14
00:00:48,160 --> 00:00:49,480
Good luck with that then.

15
00:00:49,560 --> 00:00:51,160
Yay!

16
00:00:51,240 --> 00:00:52,160
- Hey!
- Hey!

17
00:00:53,040 --> 00:00:56,160
You're such an easy target.
I love kicking your ass!

18
00:00:58,680 --> 00:01:00,520
Stop! Leave me alone.

19
00:01:00,600 --> 00:01:01,560
- Pae!
- Stop it.

20
00:01:01,640 --> 00:01:03,600
- Help me!
- I'm in a team fight!

21
00:01:06,560 --> 00:01:07,560
Don't gang up on me.

22
00:01:08,960 --> 00:01:12,280
Gosh! I died. Damn it!

23
00:01:12,360 --> 00:01:14,320
I'm nothing but a ghost.

24
00:01:15,120 --> 00:01:17,240
Enjoy chasing me, huh?

25
00:01:17,320 --> 00:01:19,880
- Hope you like my ult.
- You knew they were after you?

26
00:01:19,960 --> 00:01:22,280
They've been doing it often.

27
00:01:28,080 --> 00:01:29,680
- Man!
- Come on!

28
00:01:29,760 --> 00:01:30,760
It's over.

29
00:01:30,840 --> 00:01:32,160
Blown to pieces.

30
00:01:32,240 --> 00:01:33,640
- You suck.
- Because of you.

31
00:01:33,720 --> 00:01:35,080
I've got it!

32
00:01:44,920 --> 00:01:47,240
These are my plans to make Qin mine.

33
00:01:47,320 --> 00:01:48,440
HOW TO WIN QIN'S HEART

34
00:01:48,520 --> 00:01:50,800
Plan A is to buy snacks.

35
00:01:50,880 --> 00:01:53,600
From the latest info I got,
Qin loves eating snacks.

36
00:01:53,680 --> 00:01:54,800
How did you know?

37
00:01:54,880 --> 00:01:57,880
Back at the festival,
he had a ton of snacks.

38
00:01:57,960 --> 00:01:59,080
What's next?

39
00:01:59,160 --> 00:02:00,880
I will win him over with snacks.

40
00:02:00,960 --> 00:02:04,040
If he likes the snacks I give him,
that means he likes me.

41
00:02:04,120 --> 00:02:05,560
How much will you give?

42
00:02:05,640 --> 00:02:07,400
As much as I can afford.

43
00:02:07,480 --> 00:02:10,360
You're going all in?

44
00:02:10,440 --> 00:02:11,640
What if you fail?

45
00:02:13,400 --> 00:02:15,760
Plan B, of course!

46
00:02:15,840 --> 00:02:17,320
Scare him into loving me.

47
00:02:17,400 --> 00:02:18,800
I'll scare him with a ghost.

48
00:02:18,880 --> 00:02:21,000
Once he's scared, I'll comfort him.

49
00:02:21,080 --> 00:02:22,800
This way, he'll fall for me.

50
00:02:25,480 --> 00:02:26,400
That's weird.

51
00:02:26,480 --> 00:02:27,400
Yeah.

52
00:02:27,480 --> 00:02:30,720
How do you know
he's scared of this kind of ghost?

53
00:02:32,400 --> 00:02:35,280
You need to dress up and play your part,

54
00:02:35,360 --> 00:02:36,840
so I can do my part.

55
00:02:36,920 --> 00:02:38,840
Hell no!

56
00:02:38,920 --> 00:02:40,480
What if I get punched?

57
00:02:41,040 --> 00:02:42,240
You be the ghost!

58
00:02:42,320 --> 00:02:44,800
Who's going to help me?
I need to comfort him.

59
00:02:45,920 --> 00:02:47,160
Jamie, are you--

60
00:02:47,240 --> 00:02:48,160
Hey, stop it.

61
00:02:49,840 --> 00:02:53,920
You have to do something
he will remember for the rest of his life.

62
00:02:55,760 --> 00:02:57,760
Win him over by dressing up as a ghost.

63
00:02:57,840 --> 00:02:59,200
It's so unique.

64
00:03:00,280 --> 00:03:02,720
It's as unique as your stupidity.

65
00:03:02,800 --> 00:03:05,200
Hey, but this one's not stupid. I'm sold.

66
00:03:05,280 --> 00:03:07,520
I want him to remember every moment.

67
00:03:07,600 --> 00:03:09,120
I'm blushing.

68
00:03:09,200 --> 00:03:11,640
You two are crazy. It won't work.

69
00:03:11,720 --> 00:03:14,640
I don't think
Qin will recognize you in disguise.

70
00:03:14,720 --> 00:03:16,360
You'll terrify him.

71
00:03:18,680 --> 00:03:20,160
Then we'll go with Plan C.

72
00:03:20,720 --> 00:03:23,000
Bug him all the time.

73
00:03:23,080 --> 00:03:25,760
I'm going to be around him
at every given moment.

74
00:03:25,840 --> 00:03:27,640
What if he punches you?

75
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:32,800
I have to make sure this is safe,

76
00:03:32,880 --> 00:03:35,720
so he doesn't clobber me when he sees me.

77
00:03:36,280 --> 00:03:38,160
I acknowledge your determination

78
00:03:38,240 --> 00:03:41,280
even though all of your plans are stupid.

79
00:03:43,240 --> 00:03:44,480
I'll help.

80
00:03:44,560 --> 00:03:46,080
Me too. You can count on me.

81
00:03:46,160 --> 00:03:50,000
I want to witness your stupidity up close.

82
00:03:50,720 --> 00:03:51,840
You're so unique.

83
00:04:01,080 --> 00:04:02,720
You are. Do you get it?

84
00:04:02,800 --> 00:04:05,000
See? This is why we're friends.

85
00:04:05,080 --> 00:04:06,120
- Right.
- Yeah.

86
00:05:31,200 --> 00:05:32,720
What should I get?

87
00:05:36,680 --> 00:05:38,280
How about this one?

88
00:05:39,560 --> 00:05:40,960
That's not a snack!

89
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:43,440
How many should I get?

90
00:05:43,920 --> 00:05:45,440
As many as you can.

91
00:05:45,520 --> 00:05:47,560
Gosh, you're the real lover boy.

92
00:05:48,120 --> 00:05:49,520
I'll win his heart.

93
00:05:49,600 --> 00:05:51,240
Write him some notes too.

94
00:05:52,440 --> 00:05:53,360
Sure!

95
00:06:06,760 --> 00:06:07,600
Done! Let's go!

96
00:06:07,680 --> 00:06:09,400
We're done! Go!

97
00:06:09,480 --> 00:06:10,960
Qin is on his way to class!

98
00:06:11,040 --> 00:06:13,040
Pae, help us attach the notes!

99
00:06:13,120 --> 00:06:14,480
He'll be too full to read.

100
00:06:14,560 --> 00:06:17,000
- Help me with the notes!
- I'm working on them!

101
00:06:17,080 --> 00:06:18,600
Arrange them properly, please!

102
00:06:19,160 --> 00:06:20,440
Stop arguing!

103
00:06:20,520 --> 00:06:22,600
Why are there two here?

104
00:06:22,680 --> 00:06:24,400
- Just fix it then!
- The ice cream!

105
00:06:24,480 --> 00:06:25,320
Hurry up!

106
00:06:25,400 --> 00:06:26,320
This one?

107
00:06:26,400 --> 00:06:27,480
Shove it in!

108
00:06:27,560 --> 00:06:28,800
Go!

109
00:06:30,920 --> 00:06:31,920
I'm going now!

110
00:06:34,400 --> 00:06:37,400
Shouldn't I be the one
giving him the snacks? Hey!

111
00:06:45,400 --> 00:06:46,320
Hey!

112
00:06:48,560 --> 00:06:49,560
Hey, that's Qin.

113
00:06:53,040 --> 00:06:53,920
Come on.

114
00:06:59,400 --> 00:07:01,760
Not interested in
your so-called lover boy?

115
00:07:02,320 --> 00:07:04,200
My lover boy? No.

116
00:07:05,280 --> 00:07:07,840
If he's not yours, then whose is he?

117
00:07:10,320 --> 00:07:13,080
I need to focus on school.
I'll deal with that later.

118
00:07:13,160 --> 00:07:15,480
I feel so sorry for him.

119
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:16,920
Qin!

120
00:07:17,880 --> 00:07:19,320
I got you some snacks.

121
00:07:21,480 --> 00:07:24,640
Wait up. At least talk to him.

122
00:07:25,760 --> 00:07:27,080
What do you want me to say?

123
00:07:27,160 --> 00:07:29,840
"What brings you here, Duang?"

124
00:07:29,920 --> 00:07:31,480
How would you like me to answer?

125
00:07:31,560 --> 00:07:32,400
Enough.

126
00:07:35,920 --> 00:07:37,760
I'd say it's the wind of love.

127
00:07:40,400 --> 00:07:41,720
Go ahead and talk.

128
00:07:41,800 --> 00:07:44,440
I need to submit my assignment.
It's too hot.

129
00:07:45,240 --> 00:07:46,160
Qin.

130
00:07:47,880 --> 00:07:50,600
Will you accept these?
They're your favorites.

131
00:07:53,200 --> 00:07:54,400
How do you know?

132
00:07:54,960 --> 00:07:57,920
I saw you buying these
at the Loy Krathong Festival.

133
00:08:12,280 --> 00:08:13,360
Don't want them.

134
00:08:16,480 --> 00:08:20,480
I'll come find you later.
It's too early for me to give up.

135
00:08:20,560 --> 00:08:22,280
Prepare to be mine!

136
00:08:24,960 --> 00:08:27,080
The wind of love will find you.

137
00:09:04,680 --> 00:09:05,880
Not it.

138
00:09:05,960 --> 00:09:07,120
Or maybe Krahang?

139
00:09:09,960 --> 00:09:11,160
What about Ramphueng?

140
00:09:12,720 --> 00:09:14,520
No, Master would exorcise me.

141
00:09:15,720 --> 00:09:16,640
Maybe a zombie?

142
00:09:19,600 --> 00:09:20,520
Are you all right?

143
00:09:21,080 --> 00:09:22,000
Care to see a doctor?

144
00:09:22,080 --> 00:09:24,400
What? Why not help me then?

145
00:09:24,480 --> 00:09:26,360
I need to spook him tomorrow.

146
00:09:26,440 --> 00:09:28,280
I'm still not in the mood.

147
00:09:28,360 --> 00:09:29,840
Eat that somewhere else then.

148
00:09:29,920 --> 00:09:31,840
What? Just tell me what you need.

149
00:09:32,920 --> 00:09:35,160
What ghost should I dress up as?

150
00:09:35,240 --> 00:09:36,280
You're really doing it?

151
00:09:40,240 --> 00:09:41,440
I'll help.

152
00:09:44,440 --> 00:09:45,360
Any ideas?

153
00:09:45,440 --> 00:09:46,480
A madman?

154
00:09:46,560 --> 00:09:47,960
I'm going to smack you.

155
00:09:48,040 --> 00:09:49,400
Kuman Thong then?

156
00:09:50,280 --> 00:09:51,720
Qin will address you nicely.

157
00:09:51,800 --> 00:09:52,920
It's perfect.

158
00:09:53,000 --> 00:09:55,120
Brother Duang, can you offer me red soda?

159
00:09:55,200 --> 00:09:56,640
Brother, my ass!

160
00:09:56,720 --> 00:09:57,920
Be serious.

161
00:09:58,000 --> 00:10:00,560
How about a vampire? Pretty cool, huh?

162
00:10:03,200 --> 00:10:05,480
It is cool, but does it suit me?

163
00:10:06,760 --> 00:10:08,360
You don't like any of my ideas.

164
00:10:08,440 --> 00:10:10,040
Can you just make up your mind?

165
00:10:10,600 --> 00:10:13,760
I want a ghost that's scary but cute.

166
00:10:14,400 --> 00:10:15,920
Only one option left.

167
00:10:16,000 --> 00:10:17,080
Chucky.

168
00:10:19,920 --> 00:10:21,160
Chucky.

169
00:10:21,920 --> 00:10:22,880
Hey.

170
00:10:23,880 --> 00:10:25,600
Chucky.

171
00:10:34,640 --> 00:10:36,080
Hey, stop it!

172
00:10:47,320 --> 00:10:48,160
That's hilarious.

173
00:10:49,720 --> 00:10:51,240
- Oh, shit!
- Shit!

174
00:10:51,320 --> 00:10:52,800
You scared me.

175
00:10:52,880 --> 00:10:54,120
You nailed the costume.

176
00:10:54,200 --> 00:10:55,400
I had to.

177
00:10:55,480 --> 00:10:57,080
I'm not doing this for nothing.

178
00:10:57,160 --> 00:10:58,520
Damn, this is cool.

179
00:10:58,600 --> 00:11:02,280
How are you going to
confess your love wearing that?

180
00:11:03,960 --> 00:11:05,720
I've got it all planned out. Wait.

181
00:11:06,960 --> 00:11:08,960
What's the plan?
Do we have to do anything?

182
00:11:09,040 --> 00:11:10,880
You do. Now listen.

183
00:11:10,960 --> 00:11:13,600
Jamie, you follow Qin.

184
00:11:13,680 --> 00:11:15,920
I think he'll take his usual exit.

185
00:11:16,000 --> 00:11:18,040
I'm going to
jump out scare him over there.

186
00:11:18,120 --> 00:11:19,040
Keep me posted.

187
00:11:19,120 --> 00:11:21,400
Pae, stay with me and scout ahead.

188
00:11:22,160 --> 00:11:23,040
- Let's go.
- Okay.

189
00:11:23,120 --> 00:11:24,040
Group chant.

190
00:11:24,120 --> 00:11:25,760
Hey! Come on!

191
00:11:25,840 --> 00:11:26,840
Damn you!

192
00:11:26,920 --> 00:11:27,880
Get on with it.

193
00:11:27,960 --> 00:11:28,920
Come on, let's go.

194
00:11:39,360 --> 00:11:41,120
I have to go. I'm busy.

195
00:11:41,200 --> 00:11:42,440
Yeah, I have to go too.

196
00:11:42,520 --> 00:11:44,560
- Bye, Qin.
- See you.

197
00:11:49,400 --> 00:11:52,760
QIN IS ALL ALONE NOW

198
00:11:56,720 --> 00:11:59,240
Shit. What do I do?

199
00:12:13,720 --> 00:12:14,720
Hey!

200
00:12:14,800 --> 00:12:15,800
Why are you scared?

201
00:12:15,880 --> 00:12:17,080
It should be me.

202
00:12:18,120 --> 00:12:19,480
- Hey!
- What?

203
00:12:19,560 --> 00:12:20,640
The plan isn't working.

204
00:12:20,720 --> 00:12:21,960
Qin is coming this way.

205
00:12:22,040 --> 00:12:23,160
Get ready.

206
00:12:23,240 --> 00:12:24,800
Get ready?

207
00:12:24,880 --> 00:12:26,480
- Do I still look cute?
- No.

208
00:12:27,520 --> 00:12:28,760
Enough. Duang, just abort.

209
00:12:30,040 --> 00:12:31,920
No, you can do it. Go.

210
00:12:32,000 --> 00:12:33,160
Wait, Duang!

211
00:12:33,240 --> 00:12:34,560
Your knives.

212
00:12:34,640 --> 00:12:35,920
Shit! These look real!

213
00:12:36,000 --> 00:12:37,000
Go.

214
00:14:04,880 --> 00:14:06,080
Hey, it's me, Duang.

215
00:14:07,520 --> 00:14:09,160
You? Stop fucking clowning around!

216
00:14:09,240 --> 00:14:10,840
- Hey!
- Shit.

217
00:14:12,600 --> 00:14:13,680
I should abort the plan.

218
00:14:13,760 --> 00:14:16,800
If I scare him,
I'll probably get knocked out.

219
00:14:17,640 --> 00:14:19,760
- What?
- I don't want to do this.

220
00:14:19,840 --> 00:14:21,400
I don't want Qin to hate me.

221
00:14:21,480 --> 00:14:23,680
You said you wanted
to be a bad boy, right?

222
00:14:24,480 --> 00:14:25,680
What's the plan, Duang?

223
00:14:25,760 --> 00:14:27,480
- Qin is coming!
- I want to stop.

224
00:14:27,560 --> 00:14:28,480
Man up, come on.

225
00:14:28,560 --> 00:14:30,360
- He's gonna hate me.
- Come on!

226
00:14:31,240 --> 00:14:34,040
See? Told you. This plan is terrible!

227
00:14:34,120 --> 00:14:37,680
- He's so fucking weird.
- Let's go already.

228
00:14:40,760 --> 00:14:43,000
I'm not a ghost! This is a costume!

229
00:14:45,920 --> 00:14:48,400
It's not real! I'm a student!
I'm not a ghost.

230
00:14:49,760 --> 00:14:51,000
What? He's my friend!

231
00:14:51,560 --> 00:14:53,200
- Don't scream!
- So cute!

232
00:14:54,240 --> 00:14:55,080
That's my friend!

233
00:14:55,160 --> 00:14:57,160
- No! I'm sorry!
- That's my buddy!

234
00:14:57,240 --> 00:14:59,640
Hey, everyone is looking at us!

235
00:15:06,440 --> 00:15:07,440
Wrong way!

236
00:15:07,520 --> 00:15:09,280
Where are we going? Duang!

237
00:15:09,920 --> 00:15:11,400
Guys, I'm not a ghost!

238
00:15:11,480 --> 00:15:13,640
Calm down!
Duang! Everyone is looking at us!

239
00:15:19,600 --> 00:15:21,520
Since Plan B didn't work,

240
00:15:22,080 --> 00:15:24,360
we need to go to Plan C.

241
00:15:26,080 --> 00:15:27,040
Still at it?

242
00:15:27,120 --> 00:15:29,520
None of this sounds like
it came from a sane mind.

243
00:15:29,600 --> 00:15:30,480
No complaining.

244
00:15:30,560 --> 00:15:32,400
And cut that properly.

245
00:15:38,760 --> 00:15:39,960
What? Pae.

246
00:15:41,640 --> 00:15:42,520
Pae!

247
00:15:43,680 --> 00:15:44,560
What the heck?

248
00:15:45,560 --> 00:15:48,440
You're unbelievable, Duang.

249
00:15:49,560 --> 00:15:51,680
One complains and the other sleeps.

250
00:15:55,160 --> 00:15:56,880
It's fine. We're besties after all.

251
00:16:08,800 --> 00:16:10,160
I'm a catch, yeah?

252
00:16:10,800 --> 00:16:11,960
Man!

253
00:16:27,480 --> 00:16:29,520
I'll revolve around you.

254
00:16:32,720 --> 00:16:33,920
Qin.

255
00:16:51,280 --> 00:16:54,160
Jeez. You didn't even look at me.

256
00:16:54,240 --> 00:16:57,160
I went all out with these stickers.

257
00:17:02,800 --> 00:17:05,160
- Do you serve Americanos?
- No.

258
00:17:06,599 --> 00:17:07,640
But I'll make one.

259
00:17:07,720 --> 00:17:09,280
Please wait a sec.

260
00:17:11,480 --> 00:17:12,680
That'll be 60 baht.

261
00:17:13,359 --> 00:17:14,280
I'll scan to pay.

262
00:17:15,599 --> 00:17:16,440
Sure.

263
00:17:19,920 --> 00:17:20,760
Here you go.

264
00:17:20,839 --> 00:17:22,160
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

265
00:17:44,000 --> 00:17:45,400
It's hard to peel.

266
00:17:45,960 --> 00:17:47,120
Shit, someone's coming!

267
00:17:49,920 --> 00:17:50,840
Hurry.

268
00:18:31,040 --> 00:18:33,320
I know you're around here somewhere.

269
00:18:34,360 --> 00:18:35,320
Come on out.

270
00:18:44,560 --> 00:18:45,480
Come here.

271
00:18:49,880 --> 00:18:52,480
Do you know that
you're causing people trouble?

272
00:18:53,520 --> 00:18:54,360
Yes.

273
00:19:00,640 --> 00:19:02,560
Look, I…

274
00:19:04,240 --> 00:19:05,360
I'm sorry.

275
00:19:07,640 --> 00:19:08,920
Peel them off properly.

276
00:19:10,760 --> 00:19:14,080
And tell your little friends to help you.

277
00:19:22,920 --> 00:19:25,640
Jamie, Pae, you masterminds.

278
00:19:26,760 --> 00:19:28,720
I told you not to do it.

279
00:19:29,600 --> 00:19:31,280
Come out from behind the piano!

280
00:19:38,720 --> 00:19:39,640
- Bastard.
- Bastard.

281
00:19:45,760 --> 00:19:47,200
Peel them off properly.

282
00:19:50,080 --> 00:19:52,920
And the ones in the other building too.

283
00:19:53,720 --> 00:19:55,480
Get rid of all of them.

284
00:20:07,200 --> 00:20:08,400
That was close.

285
00:20:09,240 --> 00:20:11,520
Duang, you're nothing but trouble.

286
00:20:11,600 --> 00:20:15,600
The fact is
I'm spending all my time helping you,

287
00:20:15,680 --> 00:20:16,920
and you blamed me.

288
00:20:17,000 --> 00:20:18,080
Yeah.

289
00:20:20,560 --> 00:20:21,440
What?

290
00:20:22,080 --> 00:20:25,200
Why did you leave this part out?
Why not layer them up properly?

291
00:20:25,760 --> 00:20:26,880
What?

292
00:20:28,560 --> 00:20:30,640
It wasn't me. It was you.

293
00:20:30,720 --> 00:20:32,160
What? It wasn't me.

294
00:20:32,240 --> 00:20:33,440
You're wrong.

295
00:20:33,520 --> 00:20:35,480
No, I'm Pae, and that wasn't me.

296
00:20:35,560 --> 00:20:36,440
- It was.
- What?

297
00:20:36,520 --> 00:20:38,040
- It wasn't me.
- You're wrong.

298
00:20:38,120 --> 00:20:39,840
I'm Pae. And it wasn't me.

299
00:20:40,440 --> 00:20:41,920
- It was you.
- It was you.

300
00:20:42,000 --> 00:20:43,080
It was you.

301
00:20:43,160 --> 00:20:44,680
Jeez, just peel them off!

302
00:20:45,240 --> 00:20:46,320
Yeah.

303
00:20:50,720 --> 00:20:51,960
Jeez.

304
00:20:52,040 --> 00:20:54,720
- You're wrong.
- No, I'm Pae.

305
00:20:56,240 --> 00:20:57,720
Qin's taking forever.

306
00:20:58,520 --> 00:20:59,960
Here he comes.

307
00:21:04,520 --> 00:21:06,160
They're all over campus.

308
00:21:08,840 --> 00:21:10,000
I told him to remove them.

309
00:21:10,560 --> 00:21:12,080
When?

310
00:21:12,880 --> 00:21:15,080
- Just now.
- Right.

311
00:21:15,160 --> 00:21:16,920
So that's why you were late?

312
00:21:19,640 --> 00:21:20,560
So, how did it go?

313
00:21:20,640 --> 00:21:24,840
With how he's pursuing you,
be honest, are you uncomfortable?

314
00:21:30,040 --> 00:21:31,080
No.

315
00:21:39,440 --> 00:21:41,240
You think he's acting weird?

316
00:21:42,040 --> 00:21:43,320
I do.

317
00:21:44,600 --> 00:21:47,960
I think that this lover boy
might just have a chance.

318
00:22:02,240 --> 00:22:03,720
Why is it so hard with Qin?

319
00:22:03,800 --> 00:22:04,840
That makes one of us.

320
00:22:05,400 --> 00:22:07,120
It's never this hard for me.

321
00:22:08,200 --> 00:22:09,160
Jamie.

322
00:22:09,240 --> 00:22:11,760
You don't win people's hearts.
You just have flings.

323
00:22:11,840 --> 00:22:13,160
Get it straight.

324
00:22:15,560 --> 00:22:17,160
How should I pursue a music student?

325
00:22:17,240 --> 00:22:19,720
All three of my plans have failed.

326
00:22:20,480 --> 00:22:21,320
I got it, Duang.

327
00:22:22,120 --> 00:22:23,240
Sing for him.

328
00:22:24,000 --> 00:22:26,360
You're not bad looking.

329
00:22:27,960 --> 00:22:30,520
We're the Gigachads
of the century, anyway.

330
00:22:33,880 --> 00:22:35,880
- Just serenade him.
- No, stop.

331
00:22:37,640 --> 00:22:38,640
Not to be a buzzkill,

332
00:22:39,200 --> 00:22:41,720
but I'm pretty sure Duang can't sing.

333
00:22:44,400 --> 00:22:45,280
Do you play music?

334
00:22:45,360 --> 00:22:47,640
That's Funan's guitar.

335
00:22:51,600 --> 00:22:52,440
You play?

336
00:23:01,400 --> 00:23:02,760
One more time.

337
00:23:07,560 --> 00:23:08,760
Enough, Duang.

338
00:23:08,840 --> 00:23:10,080
It's crystal clear.

339
00:23:12,440 --> 00:23:13,600
Skip the guitar,

340
00:23:13,680 --> 00:23:16,840
or else Qin won't ever
want to talk to you.

341
00:23:17,320 --> 00:23:20,880
What do I do then?
All I've ever been good at is drawing.

342
00:23:23,400 --> 00:23:26,280
Wait! There's another thing.

343
00:23:26,840 --> 00:23:28,400
Not just drawing.

344
00:23:31,280 --> 00:23:32,600
What else?

345
00:23:34,360 --> 00:23:35,480
Liking Qin, of course.

346
00:23:39,240 --> 00:23:40,680
I'm second to none.

347
00:23:41,760 --> 00:23:42,920
What?

348
00:23:43,000 --> 00:23:44,280
It's the truth.

349
00:23:46,240 --> 00:23:47,720
I know that, sweetie.

350
00:23:49,520 --> 00:23:50,880
So what next?

351
00:23:51,440 --> 00:23:53,240
I don't know what to do about Qin.

352
00:23:55,800 --> 00:23:58,000
Even though I really like him, it's like…

353
00:23:58,880 --> 00:23:59,920
Do you feel me?

354
00:24:00,000 --> 00:24:00,840
I don't.

355
00:24:00,920 --> 00:24:01,800
Me neither.

356
00:24:03,560 --> 00:24:06,800
I understand that people fall in love,

357
00:24:07,520 --> 00:24:11,400
but why are you so madly in love with him?

358
00:24:14,960 --> 00:24:16,160
I think…

359
00:24:17,200 --> 00:24:18,640
he's totally my type.

360
00:24:19,720 --> 00:24:23,680
When I said I wanted to win his heart,
he said…

361
00:24:27,240 --> 00:24:29,080
Good luck with that then.

362
00:24:33,280 --> 00:24:34,240
<i>Guys…</i>

363
00:24:38,480 --> 00:24:41,920
he's giving me a chance.
I've gotta do my best.

364
00:24:45,000 --> 00:24:46,640
So, you're not just trying to win?

365
00:24:47,520 --> 00:24:50,480
Like, maybe he dared you or something.

366
00:24:52,960 --> 00:24:53,840
No, that's not it.

367
00:24:53,920 --> 00:24:56,200
I've never thought about winning.

368
00:24:56,280 --> 00:25:00,200
I just know that I'm really into him,
and I want to follow my heart.

369
00:25:04,320 --> 00:25:05,520
How so?

370
00:25:07,680 --> 00:25:08,600
It's like this.

371
00:25:10,040 --> 00:25:13,320
Typically, a dog barks at a plane, right?

372
00:25:14,880 --> 00:25:15,720
But suddenly…

373
00:25:17,680 --> 00:25:19,720
the plane opens its doors for the dog.

374
00:25:23,200 --> 00:25:25,400
You really made us get the picture.

375
00:25:28,640 --> 00:25:29,960
What if you can't win him over?

376
00:25:30,520 --> 00:25:31,640
I'll just cry.

377
00:25:32,880 --> 00:25:35,040
- You'll cry and move on.
- I'm not moving on.

378
00:25:35,120 --> 00:25:36,160
What?

379
00:25:36,720 --> 00:25:38,840
Once I'm done crying, I'll start over.

380
00:25:39,440 --> 00:25:42,600
Shit. What would it take
to make you quit?

381
00:25:45,280 --> 00:25:48,680
Maybe if Qin told me to stop
and chased me out of his plane.

382
00:25:52,040 --> 00:25:55,880
Or maybe,
if someone better came into his life.

383
00:25:58,360 --> 00:26:00,440
Man, that's so sick.

384
00:26:01,880 --> 00:26:02,840
But I'm the best.

385
00:26:05,200 --> 00:26:06,960
That's what makes you unique.

386
00:26:07,040 --> 00:26:09,720
Then how about you do you?

387
00:26:10,400 --> 00:26:12,000
Follow your heart.

388
00:26:12,080 --> 00:26:14,920
But there's a fine line
between pursuing and stalking.

389
00:26:15,000 --> 00:26:17,320
You gotta be genuine.

390
00:26:17,400 --> 00:26:21,320
If he's uncomfortable
with the way you're doing it,

391
00:26:21,400 --> 00:26:24,240
then you'll be a stalker in his eyes.

392
00:26:25,000 --> 00:26:30,320
I think being a straight shooter
is always best.

393
00:26:31,320 --> 00:26:33,640
For me, that's all it takes.

394
00:26:36,760 --> 00:26:38,440
That's good advice.

395
00:26:38,520 --> 00:26:39,920
If he likes you back…

396
00:26:41,000 --> 00:26:43,680
maybe he'll take you
on a first-class flight.

397
00:26:44,640 --> 00:26:46,360
Think about it, if you two work out,

398
00:26:47,080 --> 00:26:50,720
you might just be the first puppy
who gets to fly a plane!

399
00:26:52,920 --> 00:26:54,040
You copying me?

400
00:26:54,880 --> 00:26:56,000
What?

401
00:26:56,080 --> 00:26:57,200
Copying, my ass.

402
00:26:58,000 --> 00:26:59,080
Totally unrelated.

403
00:27:00,000 --> 00:27:01,240
You guys are good at this.

404
00:27:01,320 --> 00:27:03,000
Of course. We're the best.

405
00:27:03,080 --> 00:27:05,160
- Not when it's you though.
- What?

406
00:27:05,240 --> 00:27:06,320
Is that an insult?

407
00:27:06,400 --> 00:27:08,160
- It's a compliment.
- All right.

408
00:27:09,320 --> 00:27:11,120
Coaches don't play, you know?

409
00:27:11,960 --> 00:27:13,480
Because the coach is pathetic.

410
00:27:14,360 --> 00:27:15,400
Right?

411
00:27:16,840 --> 00:27:17,760
Who is?

412
00:28:24,560 --> 00:28:26,080
I've already washed my hands.

413
00:28:28,440 --> 00:28:29,720
Hello,

414
00:28:30,520 --> 00:28:32,360
this is chocolate.

415
00:28:34,320 --> 00:28:35,360
Add some enchantment.

416
00:28:35,440 --> 00:28:39,240
I am Little Duang.

417
00:28:43,840 --> 00:28:45,600
Put it here.

418
00:28:50,440 --> 00:28:51,680
Or can this suck it up?

419
00:28:56,200 --> 00:28:57,600
Trust the process.

420
00:29:03,640 --> 00:29:05,080
It opens.

421
00:29:05,160 --> 00:29:07,240
You're such a dummy, Duang.

422
00:29:16,320 --> 00:29:17,920
That's the last one.

423
00:29:21,240 --> 00:29:22,240
Let's taste it.

424
00:29:25,400 --> 00:29:26,360
Gross.

425
00:29:26,840 --> 00:29:28,960
No problem. I'll start over!

426
00:29:37,880 --> 00:29:38,800
Let me see.

427
00:29:41,160 --> 00:29:42,360
Sheesh!

428
00:29:42,440 --> 00:29:45,120
- You made those?
- That's right. Did I do good?

429
00:29:45,200 --> 00:29:46,760
- They suck.
- What?

430
00:29:46,840 --> 00:29:49,200
Just kidding. Hey, let me see.

431
00:29:49,880 --> 00:29:52,600
All that effort for this?

432
00:29:52,680 --> 00:29:54,640
Yeah, but I messed up a lot of them.

433
00:29:54,720 --> 00:29:57,880
But my feelings for Qin
are a million times more than this!

434
00:29:57,960 --> 00:29:59,920
Don't make that face.

435
00:30:00,000 --> 00:30:02,760
You guys told me
to do something Qin likes.

436
00:30:02,840 --> 00:30:06,040
He loves snacks,
so I made these for him.

437
00:30:06,520 --> 00:30:09,480
Right. Why not make them into boxes?

438
00:30:09,560 --> 00:30:10,680
What boxes?

439
00:30:11,640 --> 00:30:14,600
Blind boxes. Ever heard of them?

440
00:30:15,160 --> 00:30:16,360
How many flavors?

441
00:30:16,440 --> 00:30:17,480
Two: dark and white.

442
00:30:17,560 --> 00:30:18,760
Hey, that's perfect.

443
00:30:18,840 --> 00:30:21,240
Make blind boxes and give them to Qin.

444
00:30:21,320 --> 00:30:22,680
It'll be a total ice breaker.

445
00:30:22,760 --> 00:30:24,800
Wow, that's smart.

446
00:30:24,880 --> 00:30:29,120
This way, Duang won't be a sad pup
if Qin rejects his gifts.

447
00:30:29,200 --> 00:30:31,080
And how do I make them?

448
00:30:39,800 --> 00:30:40,800
Give those back.

449
00:30:42,480 --> 00:30:43,680
Why'd you take them?

450
00:30:47,240 --> 00:30:49,120
Aren't there any for us?

451
00:31:09,560 --> 00:31:10,800
What should we eat?

452
00:31:17,280 --> 00:31:20,880
May I have a few minutes of your time?
I'd like to ask you for a favor.

453
00:31:20,960 --> 00:31:23,240
Is this a direct sale? I'm busy.

454
00:31:24,640 --> 00:31:25,800
Your Christmas gift.

455
00:31:26,360 --> 00:31:27,840
I made it myself.

456
00:31:30,920 --> 00:31:34,360
I wanted to give you a gift
and play a game with you.

457
00:31:36,080 --> 00:31:37,400
I said I'm busy.

458
00:31:40,040 --> 00:31:41,360
Tell me when you're free.

459
00:31:41,440 --> 00:31:43,120
I'll wait right here.

460
00:31:45,080 --> 00:31:47,000
Lover boy isn't giving up, huh?

461
00:31:50,080 --> 00:31:51,920
Duang, let me tell you something.

462
00:31:52,000 --> 00:31:54,240
Approaching his friends may help.

463
00:31:54,320 --> 00:31:57,200
If you have extra,
maybe give them to us.

464
00:31:57,760 --> 00:31:59,840
Sure. Next time, consider it done.

465
00:31:59,920 --> 00:32:01,240
Don't forget about me.

466
00:32:01,320 --> 00:32:02,360
Copy that.

467
00:32:04,720 --> 00:32:06,560
If I agree to play, will you leave?

468
00:32:08,400 --> 00:32:11,040
Yes. I'll leave if you play with me.

469
00:32:14,160 --> 00:32:16,400
Go ahead. I'll catch up later.

470
00:32:17,520 --> 00:32:18,400
Here.

471
00:32:25,720 --> 00:32:26,640
You gonna play?

472
00:32:49,520 --> 00:32:50,400
What do I do?

473
00:32:52,720 --> 00:32:54,560
Here, let me explain the rules.

474
00:32:55,120 --> 00:32:58,240
If you get dark chocolate,
you can request one thing from me.

475
00:32:58,320 --> 00:33:01,400
But if it's white,
I can request one thing from you.

476
00:33:05,600 --> 00:33:06,520
Go ahead.

477
00:33:23,800 --> 00:33:26,680
White. What's your request?

478
00:33:27,680 --> 00:33:31,440
I want…

479
00:33:34,040 --> 00:33:35,760
This won't end well, will it?

480
00:33:35,840 --> 00:33:37,120
Can I walk you home?

481
00:33:49,120 --> 00:33:50,160
I like walking.

482
00:33:51,120 --> 00:33:52,800
That means more time together.

483
00:33:54,840 --> 00:33:56,400
I also like walking.

484
00:33:57,880 --> 00:33:59,560
I can even walk to Bangkok.

485
00:34:04,560 --> 00:34:07,600
Then you wait. I need to practice first.

486
00:34:09,040 --> 00:34:10,760
Yes, I can wait.

487
00:34:48,679 --> 00:34:51,639
- Please let me carry your stuff.
- I can do it myself.

488
00:34:53,920 --> 00:34:54,920
But I want to help.

489
00:34:56,159 --> 00:34:57,440
Then leave it to me.

490
00:34:59,040 --> 00:35:02,160
Right, you look so cute
when you practice.

491
00:35:02,840 --> 00:35:04,760
I'm happy to be walking with you.

492
00:35:07,520 --> 00:35:08,640
Can you do so quietly?

493
00:35:09,960 --> 00:35:10,960
Of course!

494
00:35:46,080 --> 00:35:48,280
We should take cover from the rain.

495
00:35:48,360 --> 00:35:49,600
I'll count to three,

496
00:35:49,680 --> 00:35:51,160
and we'll run over there.

497
00:35:52,840 --> 00:35:53,760
One,

498
00:35:54,480 --> 00:35:55,480
two, three!

499
00:36:01,600 --> 00:36:02,760
Qin, hurry.

500
00:36:05,880 --> 00:36:06,800
Come on, Qin.

501
00:37:01,120 --> 00:37:04,600
<i>You and me, standing way too close</i>

502
00:37:04,680 --> 00:37:07,720
<i>Feels like everything is moving slow</i>

503
00:37:07,800 --> 00:37:11,440
<i>Something inside</i>
<i>Is getting hard to hold</i>

504
00:37:11,520 --> 00:37:14,160
<i>That feeling I gotta keep low</i>

505
00:37:15,000 --> 00:37:18,400
<i>I forgot how long it has been</i>

506
00:37:18,480 --> 00:37:21,800
<i>I lost track of time so much</i>
<i>That I almost forgot to breathe</i>

507
00:37:21,880 --> 00:37:25,240
<i>We still have time</i>
<i>If you're not in a hurry</i>

508
00:37:25,320 --> 00:37:27,360
<i>Please let time slip by</i>

509
00:37:27,440 --> 00:37:31,080
<i>Just take our time</i>
<i>And let it slowly flow</i>

510
00:37:31,160 --> 00:37:34,480
<i>Stay a little longer</i>
<i>Don't leave me here alone</i>

511
00:37:34,560 --> 00:37:37,920
<i>Just want to be with you</i>
<i>Even if we're stuck in the rain</i>

512
00:37:38,000 --> 00:37:41,480
<i>I just want to be here</i>
<i>'Cause you make me feel at home</i>

513
00:37:41,560 --> 00:37:44,840
<i>I can feel your heartbeat</i>

514
00:37:44,920 --> 00:37:48,360
<i>Every time you breathe</i>

515
00:37:48,440 --> 00:37:51,800
<i>I don't know if we'll ever</i>
<i>Get to have this moment again</i>

516
00:37:51,880 --> 00:37:55,280
<i>So please, don't leave this place</i>

517
00:39:00,160 --> 00:39:02,040
There you go. Satisfied?

518
00:39:03,960 --> 00:39:04,840
Of course.

519
00:39:04,920 --> 00:39:06,040
Leave then.

520
00:39:07,800 --> 00:39:08,920
Hey!

521
00:39:12,160 --> 00:39:13,880
Can you follow me back on IG?

522
00:39:16,440 --> 00:39:17,880
You said only one request.

523
00:39:21,520 --> 00:39:22,960
Can we play again then?

524
00:39:24,880 --> 00:39:26,200
No, I don't want to.

525
00:39:27,800 --> 00:39:28,920
Please play!

526
00:39:29,000 --> 00:39:31,760
I have so many chocolates at my place.
Are you sure?

527
00:39:31,840 --> 00:39:33,000
We can play way more.

528
00:39:33,080 --> 00:39:34,080
No.

529
00:39:35,200 --> 00:39:37,560
You like chocolate, don't you?

530
00:39:38,040 --> 00:39:42,280
I have tons I can bring for you.
Please play with me!

531
00:39:47,720 --> 00:39:48,640
Don't push it.

532
00:39:56,200 --> 00:39:59,200
New information acquired:
this is Qin's condo.

533
00:39:59,280 --> 00:40:00,600
My boyfriend's place!

534
00:40:00,680 --> 00:40:02,280
My future boyfriend…

535
00:40:12,640 --> 00:40:15,560
<i>If you get dark chocolate,</i>
<i>you can request one thing from me.</i>

536
00:40:15,640 --> 00:40:18,960
<i>But if it's white,</i>
<i>I can request one thing from you.</i>

537
00:41:30,760 --> 00:41:31,720
Hey, everyone.

538
00:41:33,640 --> 00:41:35,640
- Hello, Coach.
- Hi.

539
00:41:38,920 --> 00:41:40,960
Hey, what about PK?

540
00:41:45,880 --> 00:41:46,840
I'm here, Coach.

541
00:41:54,480 --> 00:41:55,800
You're late again.

542
00:41:57,320 --> 00:42:00,640
All right, let's practice.
Start warming up.

543
00:42:20,440 --> 00:42:21,960
Sprint and touch the line.

544
00:42:50,920 --> 00:42:53,360
All right, let's take ten. Go.

545
00:43:05,760 --> 00:43:06,960
Right, Qin.

546
00:43:07,040 --> 00:43:08,440
How was it with Duang?

547
00:43:10,200 --> 00:43:12,680
Why did he walk you home?
I'm confused.

548
00:43:13,240 --> 00:43:14,640
That's all it was.

549
00:43:16,000 --> 00:43:18,520
- You took the same route?
- No.

550
00:43:18,600 --> 00:43:20,760
So you're warming up to him?

551
00:43:22,120 --> 00:43:23,000
What?

552
00:43:23,080 --> 00:43:25,080
No, it's just,

553
00:43:25,160 --> 00:43:28,520
if you are,
I'll give him your class schedule.

554
00:43:29,000 --> 00:43:30,640
He asks for it every day.

555
00:43:32,600 --> 00:43:33,480
We'll see.

556
00:43:35,200 --> 00:43:36,840
You're gonna be friends for now?

557
00:43:37,880 --> 00:43:41,080
Not friends.
I don't let friends pursue me.

558
00:43:41,160 --> 00:43:42,360
Friends are friends.

559
00:43:43,000 --> 00:43:46,080
If someone doesn't want friendship,
they shouldn't approach me that way.

560
00:43:47,840 --> 00:43:50,640
Okay. That's not sus at all.

561
00:43:51,280 --> 00:43:53,000
Qin knows what he wants.

562
00:43:59,320 --> 00:44:01,520
Come on, let's practice.

563
00:44:01,600 --> 00:44:05,320
When he said, "We'll see." Does that mean
I should give Duang his schedule?

564
00:44:06,760 --> 00:44:10,360
Maybe he'll do it. Just stay out of it.

565
00:44:12,840 --> 00:44:13,760
You're right.

566
00:44:22,320 --> 00:44:24,200
This isn't right, Jamie.

567
00:44:24,280 --> 00:44:26,720
Do you think they're exploiting us?

568
00:44:26,800 --> 00:44:29,520
Why did you stop?
Just keep going. It's heavy!

569
00:44:31,040 --> 00:44:32,560
That's why I stopped.

570
00:44:33,440 --> 00:44:34,360
It's too heavy.

571
00:44:35,600 --> 00:44:37,200
Hey, Duang!

572
00:44:41,320 --> 00:44:42,440
Hey, what is it?

573
00:44:42,520 --> 00:44:43,360
These are heavy.

574
00:44:43,440 --> 00:44:44,600
Hold this.

575
00:44:44,680 --> 00:44:46,040
Guys, sorry for troubling you.

576
00:44:46,120 --> 00:44:47,040
What's your deal?

577
00:44:48,240 --> 00:44:49,200
Yeah.

578
00:44:50,440 --> 00:44:51,760
- Come on!
- Are you all right?

579
00:44:51,840 --> 00:44:53,360
Pae, stop playing dumb.

580
00:44:59,760 --> 00:45:02,600
You're gonna wear out the word "cute."

581
00:45:10,760 --> 00:45:11,960
Duang!

582
00:45:13,920 --> 00:45:15,760
My name is Alice.

583
00:45:15,840 --> 00:45:18,800
Our university is having an open house.

584
00:45:18,880 --> 00:45:22,840
This means
there will be a ton of visitors.

585
00:45:23,600 --> 00:45:24,440
I'm sorry?

586
00:45:25,160 --> 00:45:30,600
Well… I'd like you to dance
at the opening for the open house.

587
00:45:31,680 --> 00:45:33,440
I'm afraid I can't do that.

588
00:45:34,760 --> 00:45:35,840
Duang.

589
00:45:35,920 --> 00:45:39,720
I expected to hear a "yes" from you.

590
00:45:39,800 --> 00:45:42,440
You're my only option, Duang.

591
00:45:42,520 --> 00:45:45,160
I can't sing, you see.

592
00:45:45,240 --> 00:45:48,240
My friends say I'm tone-deaf.
I can't dance either.

593
00:45:48,320 --> 00:45:49,880
So how would I be of any help?

594
00:45:50,440 --> 00:45:53,040
Please, Duang. I need your help.

595
00:45:53,120 --> 00:45:55,520
I'm out of options.

596
00:45:56,000 --> 00:45:58,160
I do have a friend
who is really good-looking.

597
00:45:58,240 --> 00:46:00,640
His name's Jamie, and he can sing.
He's a better option.

598
00:46:00,720 --> 00:46:01,880
He's probably around there.

599
00:46:03,040 --> 00:46:05,560
What? Jamie? I know him.

600
00:46:05,640 --> 00:46:09,000
He does whatever he wants.
He's not reliable.

601
00:46:09,080 --> 00:46:12,400
There's only you,
my adorable little Duang.

602
00:46:13,640 --> 00:46:15,560
I'm not adorable. I'm handsome.

603
00:46:19,040 --> 00:46:20,120
Yes, you're right!

604
00:46:20,200 --> 00:46:21,520
You're extremely handsome.

605
00:46:21,600 --> 00:46:23,640
You're the most handsome guy there is.

606
00:46:23,720 --> 00:46:28,480
Since I was born,
I've never met anyone so perfect.

607
00:46:30,200 --> 00:46:33,720
Trust me. I'm right about this.

608
00:46:33,800 --> 00:46:37,120
Anyway, please get back to me.

609
00:46:37,200 --> 00:46:38,640
Don't keep me waiting.

610
00:46:39,280 --> 00:46:40,120
But--

611
00:46:40,200 --> 00:46:43,080
If you don't want to do it for me,

612
00:46:43,160 --> 00:46:46,160
then do it for our university.

613
00:46:46,880 --> 00:46:49,400
I really can't do this.

614
00:46:49,480 --> 00:46:50,640
I could ruin everything.

615
00:46:50,720 --> 00:46:52,240
You won't be alone.

616
00:46:54,200 --> 00:46:55,320
I knew you'd be lonely.

617
00:46:55,400 --> 00:46:57,800
That's why I got you a partner.

618
00:46:59,600 --> 00:47:01,880
I really can't do this.

619
00:47:03,280 --> 00:47:04,880
It's that guy.

620
00:47:06,040 --> 00:47:07,920
Hey! How did you get in here?

621
00:47:08,000 --> 00:47:09,480
Get out! We're practicing!

622
00:47:13,080 --> 00:47:14,040
I can do it!

623
00:47:14,120 --> 00:47:15,240
What? For real?

624
00:47:15,320 --> 00:47:16,440
Let's get started.

625
00:47:16,520 --> 00:47:17,800
Let me call my professor.

626
00:47:17,880 --> 00:47:18,920
Don't bail on me.

627
00:47:19,000 --> 00:47:19,840
Promise?

628
00:47:19,920 --> 00:47:22,160
Yes. Let's do this. Let's go.

629
00:47:24,000 --> 00:47:25,880
Wait, you two know each other?

630
00:47:27,680 --> 00:47:28,560
- We don't.
- We do.

631
00:47:29,760 --> 00:47:31,640
What's going on?

632
00:47:32,480 --> 00:47:33,360
That's okay.

633
00:47:33,440 --> 00:47:36,200
Now you two know each other, right?

634
00:47:36,280 --> 00:47:39,000
And soon, you'll be
rehearsing together a lot.

635
00:48:01,000 --> 00:48:07,640
I'M PREPARED TO LOVE YOU
WITH EVERYTHING I HAVE!

636
00:48:26,000 --> 00:48:29,160
This is Duang and Qin.
They'll join us on stage.

637
00:48:29,240 --> 00:48:30,800
I won't let you down.

638
00:48:30,880 --> 00:48:31,720
I totally forgot.

639
00:48:31,800 --> 00:48:33,560
I won't get to see Qin during break.

640
00:48:35,320 --> 00:48:38,880
<i>If you want to see him,</i>
<i>come up with an excuse then.</i>

641
00:48:38,960 --> 00:48:40,280
Should we grab some food?

642
00:48:41,680 --> 00:48:43,520
The ship isn't sinking anymore.

643
00:48:45,040 --> 00:48:46,840
That's 100,000 points for our lover boy.

644
00:48:47,720 --> 00:48:48,800
<i>Stop with that tone.</i>

645
00:48:48,880 --> 00:48:49,960
<i>I can't do that.</i>

646
00:48:50,520 --> 00:48:52,080
I'm just so into you.
